Text.Value: What is going on in your basement? There's masks, mushrooms - all the signs of a hag.
Welcome back, mate. What can I get you?
*Magic tickles your senses, the same you felt around the Flaming Fist in Basilisk Gate. Someone, or something, has tampered with his memory.*
Didn't think a tough guy like you would be scared of a little knife.
Then piss in your cup - like the rest of us.

EditorData.NodeContext: saying it like it's painfully obvious

Text.Value: *Magic tickles your senses. Someone, or something, has tampered with his memory.*
Can I see your wares?
Captain Grisly is dead. My only comfort is that you offed her killer - a godsdamned hag, of all things.

EditorData.NodeContext: sad, trying to be grateful but sturggling

Text.Value: Captain said you're one of us now. So, far as I'm concerned, you're part of the crew, mate. Welcome to the 'Maid.
I'd love to see you try and kick me out.
Then I'm glad. The Captain didn't take orders from nothing or nobody. She'd have picked death over the hag any day.
Leave.
Bloody hells, that was some ruckus. I catch you fighting any more drunks, I'll toss ye all outside. Even if they did deserve a clatter.
A... redcap? One of 'em pointy looking fuckers? You know, I thought I saw - urgh.

EditorData.NodeContext: confused, dazed, trying to remember (then wince of pain at end and touches head) he's been put under a spell by the hag

Text.Value: Don't be. You weren't the one who was supposed to protect her.
Who pulled a knife on you?
Aye - and I didn't lift a finger to save her. It was like I was stuck in a fog, my mind addled from every direction.
Not a clue - my head is still melted. Feels like I've been sucking on fog for days.
If this is a joke, you're missing the punchline. Basement has four walls and some shelves, mate - was down there just this morning.
Wishing you fair winds, mate.
Gods above - not again. You pull a knife on me like the last one, and you're getting the boot - you hear?
Is your captain all right? I saved her from the hag.
I think I killed the real Captain - she was under the hag's control.
But, uh, keep working on the comedy routine, yeah?
Use your eyes.
That woman 'Lara', or 'Lora', whatever her bloody name is. She was screaming her head off about some kid -  tore the place apart. Bloody disturbing.

EditorData.NodeContext: he's a tough man, but he's clearly shook up

Text.Value: Sorry, mate, only red in here is my patrons' faces when they've had a few too many. Take it easy, yeah?

EditorData.NodeContext: snaps back, confusion gone - jovial smile

Text.Value: Aye - take your time.
All I know is I had one job - protect my Captain. And I failed.
'Lara', or 'Lora', was her name. Started tearing the place apart, screaming about some kid. Bloody disturbing it was.

EditorData.NodeContext: he's a tough man, but he's clearly shook up

Text.Value: Ah here, mate - I know the Captain is a bit of a battleaxe, but a 'hag'? Yer out of line.
What do you sell here?
If yer here to complain' that the booze tastes like piss - I know. Anything else?
Any trade available to a heroic hag-killer?
Enjoy the Blushing Mermaid.
I'll follow the rules.
I'm sorry I couldn't save her.
I'm here about the missing girl - Vanra?
You need to leave - Captain Grisly is a hag.
Won't be no need so long as you don't try to shank me, or start screaming about vanishing children.
How'd she get captured in the first place?
*His eyes glaze over as the spell takes effect - his memory lost.*
Can I see your wares?
Good. Welcome to the Blushing Mermaid.

EditorData.NodeContext: sigh, already done with the player

Text.Value: 'Lara' or 'Lora' or whatever it was learned that lesson the hard way.
It's a sad day in the 'Maid. A sad and bloody day.
I didn't fight drunks - I fought redcaps.
You saw her change too?! I tried to gut her but she - she dug her claws in me and - urgh.
I've killed people with a splinter, mate. 'Course I'm wary of a blade.
No pissin' or shittin'. If ya break it, ya pay for it. Any fightin' and Captain Grisly will shank ya. Got it?

EditorData.NodeContext: the tone of a man who's dealt with many, many drunkards and is tired

Text.Value: If you must.
She left me the 'Maid. And while it won't be the same without her, know you're always welcome here, mate.

EditorData.NodeContext: heavy sigh, affection at the end

Text.Value: All I could hear was a voice telling me the Captain was safe and well upstairs. Gives me the willies just thinking about it.

EditorData.NodeContext: a slight smile at the threat - he knows it's the captains why of showing thanks

Text.Value: Captain Grisly had to clock her in the end - threw her out on her arse. Good riddance.
What if I really really need to use the latrine?

Synopsis: Bosun Gannet runs the bar at the Blushing Mermaid - he is a tough, no nonsense pirate who's spending his twilight years working for his Captain as a bartender.
